                        'description' => "<h3>Overview</h3>\n<p>Embark on an unforgettable journey through Egypt’s fascinating past with a tour that showcases two of the country’s most remarkable landmarks: the Grand Egyptian Museum and the Pyramids of Giza. Begin your adventure at the Grand Egyptian Museum, the largest archaeological museum in the world dedicated to a single civilization. Explore its impressive galleries featuring thousands of priceless artifacts from ancient Egypt, including the complete treasures of King Tutankhamun, magnificent statues, royal relics, and exceptional masterpieces spanning thousands of years of history. Your expert Egyptologist guide will bring these ancient wonders to life with captivating stories of pharaohs, gods, and the rise of one of the world’s greatest civilizations. Continue to the legendary Pyramids of Giza, where you will stand before the Great Pyramid of Khufu, the last surviving Wonder of the Ancient World. Explore the magnificent Giza Plateau and admire the pyramids of Khafre and Menkaure before visiting the mysterious Great Sphinx, the iconic guardian of the pyramids. Take in breathtaking panoramic views of this extraordinary archaeological site and capture unforgettable photographs of Egypt’s most famous monuments. This full-day excursion offers the perfect blend of history, culture, and awe-inspiring landmarks, making it an essential experience for anyone visiting Egypt.</p>\n<h3>Trip Highlights</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Visit the spectacular Grand Egyptian Museum (GEM).</li>\n  <li>Discover the treasures of King Tutankhamun and ancient Egyptian masterpieces.</li>\n  <li>Explore the iconic Pyramids of Giza.</li>\n  <li>See the legendary Great Sphinx.</li>\n  <li>Enjoy fascinating insights from a professional Egyptologist guide.</li>\n  <li>Capture stunning panoramic views of the Giza Plateau.</li>\n</ul>",
